results.message: GH_API_TOKEN environment variable must be defined to test github backend
GH_API_TOKEN environment variable must be defined to test github backend

tests.name:
test_section_numbering_enabled[preceding
# This is the first section
Hello from first section.
## This is the first subsection
Hello from first of top.
# This is the second section
Hello from second section.
## This is the second subsection
Hello from first of second.
#### This is a deeper section
More Stuff
## This is the third subsection
Hello from second of second.
-context1-preceding
# 1 This is the first section
Hello from first section.
## 1.1 This is the first subsection
Hello from first of top.
# 2 This is the second section
Hello from second section.
## 2.1 This is the second subsection
Hello from first of second.
#### 2.1.1.1 This is a deeper section
More Stuff
## 2.2 This is the third subsection
Hello from second of second.
]
test_section_numbering_disabled[{% if fruit is defined %}banana{% endif %}-context1-]
test_section_numbering_disabled[{% if fruit is defined %}banana{% endif %}-context2-banana\n]

test_vocabulary[apple
banana
cherry
{% for vocab in first_pass_output.words | sort %}[{{ vocab }}]{% endfor %}-apple
banana
cherry
[apple][banana][cherry]
]

test_vocabulary[apple banana cherry
{% if first_pass_output.has('banana') %}banana: yellow fruit
{% endif %}-apple banana cherry
banana: yellow fruit
]

test_vocabulary[apple Banana cherry
{% if first_pass_output.has_ignore_case('banana') %}banana: yellow fruit
{% endif %}-apple Banana cherry
banana: yellow fruit
]
